Subject: Re: [T2] where is tdc

On Monday, July 10, 2006, at 12:01PM, richard carlton <browndog32(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:

>on a 1978 2.0 FI , is tdc when the intake valve closes completely.  i have
>obsereved the valves while i turn the bolt on the alternaotor.  it does not
>seem that the notch is lining up with o at that point.  just after the
>intake valve closes( comes to the top).   when is tdc according to the
>valves.

It's when both valves are closed. As the rotate the engine clockwise from TDC you will notice the exhaust valve opening. Rotate CCW and you'll see the intake open.

